   "source": ["# Week 2 Lecture: Isaac Lab, Parallel GPU Training, and PPO at Scale\n", "\n", "Note: Isaac Lab's environments must run as a single continuous script, not step-by-step in a live kernel (this is a real, documented Isaac Lab limitation, not a mistake). So each cell below runs a real script as a subprocess and shows you its actual output — you still get one scrollable lesson document, just via  shell cells instead of live Python state."]
  },
  {
